<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-68-0242 </DOCNO><TEXT>The difficult and variable rock-mechanical conditions at Osterfeld collierynecessitated conversion from selective cutting to conventional drivage,as the latter technology is better adoptable to the varying rock-mechanicalproblems encountered when undercutting pillar edges. Full backfillingat the face is required in order to prevent road convergence. The articledescribes the drivage of a belt road with a clearance of 20.5m/sup 2/,a floor width of 6m, and a height of 4.3m. 1240m were driven in 10 months,amounting to a meterage of 6.04m/d. (MOS)</TEXT></DOC>